            <title>[SOLR-1005] DoubleMetaphone Filter Produces NullpointerException on zero-length token</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1005</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If any token given to the DoubleMetaphoneFilter is empty (Token exists, 0 length), then the encoder will return null instead of a metaphone encoded string. The current code assumes that there will always be a valid object returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed solution: Make sure 0-length tokens are skipped at the top branch where the code checks whether or not we have a Token object at all.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;jdk 1.6.10, tomcat 6.x&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
